      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne bot. Garden ¶ 9/9/64. ¶ Sir ¶  ¶ I have the honor to solicit that you will be pleased to advance to me from the treasury the sum of thirty pounds sterling (£30), which amount you desired me ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">64.09.09</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To James McCulloch</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">K64/9168, unit 49, VPRS 3991/P inward registered correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne bot. Garden</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">9/9/64.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have the honor to solicit that you will be pleased to advance to me from the treasury the sum of thirty pounds sterling (£30), which amount you desired me to expend in processing seeds of forest trees in this country for the Madras Government.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honor to be,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sir,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>your most obedient servant</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. Mueller</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M.D.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">The honorable the Chief Secretary<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">On 26 August 1864 the Governor's office had written to M to authorize a sum of £30 to be spent on seeds for Madras (letter not found; acknowledged in M to H. Warde, 27 August 1864).</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>On 14 September 1864 the Under Secretary, J. Moore, minuted 'The Director of the Botanic Gardens is informed that the sum he requires will be advanced to him by the Treasury on his signing the enclosed application and returning it to this office.' M returned the application the next day adding: 'Signed accordingly with thanks';<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Moore instructed: 'Advance application for £30 counter signed and forwarded to the Honble the Treasurer.' On 29 September 1864 E.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>S. Symonds<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">minuted</seg>: 'Returned to the Under Secy — The advance act. [account] has been<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">[posted</seg>]<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>for payment.'</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">The availability of the seeds for shipment was notified in<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>to J. McCulloch, 12 September 1864<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">(in this edition as 64-09-12b)</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">.</seg>
                     </p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; color: #C00000; "
                        xml:lang="en">I am almost certain that posted will be correct; do we need [ ]?</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
         </div>
      </body>
